* HOTP\n(RFC 4226)
** Construction
*** HOTP(K, C) = Truncate(HMAC-SHA-1(K, C))
*** K: shared secret (>=128b, 160b rec.)
*** C: 8-byte counter (moving factor)
*** Dynamic truncation
**** offset = low 4 bits of HS[19]
**** 4-byte window, mask top bit
**** DBC mod 10^d (d >= 6)
** Design goals (R1-R6)
*** Sequence/counter-based
*** Cheap, no keypad needed
*** Short, readable code
*** Strong shared secret
** Validation
*** Look-ahead window s
*** Resync counter on match
*** Throttling T / delay scheme
*** Optional value sequence
** Security analysis
*** Bits-to-digits bias negligible
*** Brute force is optimal
*** Sec = s*v / 10^d
*** HMAC-SHA-1 PRF assumption
*** SHA-1 collisions do not affect HMAC
** Extensions
*** More digits / alphanumeric
*** Counter-based resync
*** Data field
**** Timer as moving factor
**** => TOTP (RFC 6238)
@endmindmap
